    ],
    "abstractNote": "In this article, I examine the mysticism of Bar Hebraeus according to the metaphysical positions taken within the academic study of mysticism, positions which reveal the different schools of thought within that field of study. I further consider how the mystic discourse of Bar Hebraeus can offer a corrective to such presuppositions. Thus, Bar Hebraeus drew on the Syrian monastic spirituality of the 'love of God', to critique the scholastic metaphysics of Aristotelian philosophy that had risen to prominence in the Avicennan tradition of Islamic philosophy; a critique which is also relevant for contemporary conceptions of the metaphysics of mysticism.",
